{
  "text": "Neurol Sci (2013) 34 (Suppl 1):S101-S108 inpatient management, it is limited in use for outpatient care. DHE administered via currently available nasal preparations has a slow onset of action, low bioavailability of about 40 %, and is less effective than nasal and subcutaneous sumatriptan [CITATION_1] . Intramuscular and subcutaneous dihydroergotamine is more effective, but produces somewhat more adverse effects and the mode of administration is less convenient. A new oral DHE inhalation device, Levadex, has been demonstrated to provide similar onset of action and efficacy comparable to intravenous DHE. The device delivers DHE deep into the lung automatically after breath actuation. A phase I study of DHE delivered by the inhaler vs. 1 mg of IV DHE was performed and revealed there was a rapid systemic absorption of DHE with a time to maximum concentration (t max ) of 12 min with a 0.88 mg respirable dose (vs. a 6 min t max with the IV preparation) [CITATION_2] . The ratio of AUC 0-? of inhaled vs. IV was approximately 0.77, revealing slightly lower systemic levels of inhaled DHE than IV DHE. Phase II data found that 32 % of patients receiving 0.5 mg doses achieved pain relief as early as 10 min (p = 0.019) with a low incidence of side effects including nausea and no clinically significant change in pulmonary function tests, clinical lab findings, heart rate, blood pressure or respiratory rate [CITATION_3] . Phase III trials demonstrated quick onset (pain relief was achieved in 30 min) and very good efficacy, with acute pain relief (58.7 % of Levadex patients vs. 34.5 % for placebo, p = 0.0001) with low incidence of side effects, including nausea (4.5 vs. 2 %) and vomiting (2 vs. 0.1 %) [CITATION_4] . This study also demonstrated a sustained pain freedom with a very low 6.5 % recurrence rate at 24 h and 10.3 % recurrence rate at 48 h. This is notable especially when compared to two metaanalyses that have calculated the cumulative 24 h recurrence rate for triptans in general to between 22 and 29 %.",
  "correct_citation": {
